)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Units"/Topi1:"Watt/sec"/Type1:"K"/Diff1:"M"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"Watt/sec is a unit of"
A:"c"
O:a)"momentum",b)"force",c)"energy",d)"power"
R:"Watt = J/s, so Watt×sec = Joule (energy). Watt/sec is not standard, but among options 'energy' is the intended answer."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Mechanics"/Topi1:"Pulleys"/Type1:"K"/Diff1:"E"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"A fixed pulley is employed to"
A:"b"
O:a)"do more work with the same force but without using pulley",b)"change the direction of force",c)"same work",d)"have mechanical advantage greater than one"
R:"Fixed pulley only changes direction, MA=1."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Friction"/Topi1:"Types"/Type1:"K"/Diff1:"E"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"The force of friction that comes into action after the motion has started is known as"
A:"a"
O:a)"dynamic friction",b)"static friction",c)"friction only",d)"limiting friction"
R:"Dynamic (kinetic) friction acts during motion."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Rotational Motion"/Topi1:"Rolling"/Type1:"U"/Diff1:"M"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"Let a disc, a cylinder, a solid sphere, and a ring be rolled down in an inclined plane simultaneously. Which will reach first?"
A:"c"
O:a)"disc",b)"cylinder",c)"solid sphere",d)"ring"
R:"Solid sphere has smallest moment of inertia per mass → greatest acceleration."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Vectors"/Topi1:"Resultant"/Type1:"A"/Diff1:"M"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"Forces of 3N, 4N and 12N act at a point in mutually perpendicular direction. The magnitude of the resultant force in newton is"
A:"a"
O:a)"13",b)"11",c)"5",d)"indeterminate from the information given"
R:"Resultant = √(3²+4²+12²) = √169 = 13."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Work Energy"/Topi1:"Work Conditions"/Type1:"K"/Diff1:"E"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"Which of the following is not necessary for work to be done?"
A:"d"
O:a)"an applied force",b)"a force component along the displacement",c)"a displacement",d)"a constant speed"
R:"Work requires force and displacement in direction of force; constant speed is not required."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Mechanics"/Topi1:"Energy"/Type1:"K"/Diff1:"E"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"A body at rest may have"
A:"d"
O:a)"speed",b)"momentum",c)"velocity",d)"energy"
R:"A body at rest can have potential or internal energy."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Vectors"/Topi1:"Force Properties"/Type1:"K"/Diff1:"E"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"We know that forces are vectors because"
A:"a"
O:a)"they obey the same mathematical rules that displacement obey",b)"they are defined in such a way that they are vectors",c)"they always add to zero",d)"they have magnitude"
R:"Forces add by the parallelogram law, like displacements."
)

Subj1:"Physics"/Chap1:"Kinematics"/Topi1:"Acceleration"/Type1:"A"/Diff1:"E"/Stem1:""/(
Q:"A car accelerates for 10s at 6m/s2. What is its final seed if its initial was 4m/s2"
A:"b"
O:a)"34m/s",b)"64m/s",c)"60m/s",d)"30m/s"
R:"v = u + at = 4 + 6×10 = 64 m/s."
)

